      "amount": "pinch"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a tagine or heavy‑bottomed pot over medium heat.",
    "Add sliced bell pepper and sauté for 3–4 minutes until just softened.",
    "Stir in cumin, coriander, cinnamon, and cayenne (if using) and cook for 30 seconds to bloom the spices.",
    "Pour in honey and lemon juice, stirring to coat the pepper; let the mixture simmer for 2 minutes.",
    "Reduce heat to low, then fold in ricotta cheese and chopped dates; stir until ricotta melts and the sauce thickens, about 5 minutes.",
    "Season with salt to taste and garnish with fresh cilantro before serving.",
    "Serve hot with a side of warm flatbread or a simple grain like couscous (omit if strictly FODMAP)."
  ],
